#: ../../../docs/terminal-sessions.rst:3
msgid "Terminal sessions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/terminal-sessions.rst:5
msgid ""
"Pygments support the parsing and highlighting of terminal sessions, like "
"command-line shells, interactive consoles and language `REPL <https://en."
"wikipedia.org/wiki/Read–eval–print_loop>`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/terminal-sessions.rst:9
msgid "They are typically command lines or code, mixed with generic output."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/terminal-sessions.rst:11
msgid ""
"Examples for each can be found in the :doc:`lexer <lexers>` documentation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/terminal-sessions.rst:15
msgid "Operating system shells"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/terminal-sessions.rst:17
msgid ""
"These lexers are expecting a prompt to identify user input. So to highlight "
"a shell session, prefix your code snippet with a specially formatted prompt."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/terminal-sessions.rst:20
msgid "They are typically named ``<shell> Session``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/terminal-sessions.rst:24
msgid "Interactive consoles"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/terminal-sessions.rst:26
msgid ""
"Similarly to systems shells, Pygments recognize a variety of interactive "
"language sessions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/terminal-sessions.rst:29
msgid ""
"Their IDs typically follow the ``<language>-console`` or ``<language>-repl`` "
"pattern."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/terminal-sessions.rst:34
msgid "Generic output"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/terminal-sessions.rst:36
msgid ""
"To display standalone terminal output and keep styling consistent, you can "
"use the generic ``output`` lexer."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/terminal-sessions.rst:41
msgid "ANSI rendering"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/terminal-sessions.rst:43
msgid ""
"In all the lexers above, the command results are parsed as generic output. "
"Which means they are rendered as-is, without any styling applied, for "
"example by ANSI codes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/terminal-sessions.rst:46
msgid "Here is a couple of third-party projects covering this use-case:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/terminal-sessions.rst:48
msgid ""
"`pygments-ansi-color <https://github.com/chriskuehl/pygments-ansi-color>`_: "
"implements a new lexer and formatter to parse and render pure ANSI content."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/terminal-sessions.rst:51
msgid ""
"`Click Extra <https://github.com/kdeldycke/click-extra>`_: adds `ANSI-"
"capable lexers <https://kdeldycke.github.io/click-extra/pygments.html#ansi-"
"language-lexers>`_ for each language listed above."
msgstr ""
